The paper deals with the problem of estimating a high-dimensional vector of parameters from noisy observations, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), statistics (cs.ST), and data science (cs.DS). The proposed method involves clustering the components of the observed vector and shrinking each cluster towards a common attractor, which is a technique commonly used in unsupervised learning and clustering (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.DS, and cs.SI, in that order.
